fields.value: Centro de Investigaciones sobre la realidad Social (CIRES) [Spain], 1992 (M534V1)

authorName.value: Centro de Estudios sobre la Realidad Social

dsDescriptionValue.value:
The CIRES studies are conducted over a period of months in 1992. In 1992 the studies explore supranational identification, attitudes toward science and technology, attitudes toward immigrants, justice and civic rights, old age, political and economic culture, ecology and environment, social ethics, and mass media. Studies are conducted under the supervision of Juan Diez Nicols.

Sample for all months: 1,200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted from January to December, through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Redex Network (IOPE-ETMAR). Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.
